uiet Revolution? Can we say that loyalty to the team constitutes a religion for its fans? How is corporatization affecting how Quebecers connect with their beloved team? Featuring a wide range of writing on Le Grand Club and its social significance, the book offers a fresh and fascinating perspective on one of Canada’s greatest sports teams.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aHockey fanszQuébec (Province). 0aHockey playerszQuébec (Province). 0aHockeyxSocial aspectszQuébec (Province). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aBauer, Olivier, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCha, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeneault, Alain, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaberge, Suzanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaurin-Lamothe, Audrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaurin-Lamothe, Audrey, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMoreau, Nicolas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoreau, Nicolas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNahas, Chloé, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRivest, Marie-Pier, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRivest, Marie-Pier.1 aScott, Howard.1 aValois-Nadeau, Fannie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311060681240uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144261749040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442617490423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442617490.jpg  a978-3-11-060681-2  University of Toronto Press